  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "IT System Administrator",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Perform Microsoft 365 and Azure administration, including:</p><ul><li><p>Intune, Entra ID, Exchange, SharePoint, Teams, Defender, and security configuration</p></li><li><p>PowerShell scripting for automation and administration tasks</p></li></ul></li><li><p>Provide Level 1.5 support for Microsoft 365 issues and escalations</p></li><li><p>Manage and support Intune and Entra, including:</p><ul><li><p>Application packaging for deployment and removal</p></li><li><p>Configuration and Compliance Policies</p></li><li><p>Conditional Access configuration</p></li><li><p>Scripts and remediation activities</p></li><li><p>Application protection and AppLocker deployment</p></li><li><p>Device enrollment and device administration</p></li></ul></li><li><p>Provide support for:</p><ul><li><p>Windows endpoints (laptops/desktops)</p></li><li><p>Printers and peripherals</p></li><li><p>Basic network devices (routers, switches, access points)</p></li></ul></li><li><p>Participate in MS 365, network, and infrastructure projects and implementations</p></li><li><p>Research, diagnose, and resolve new or evolving technical issues independently<br /></p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><p>Hands-on experience in independent MS 365 administration</p></li><li><p>Strong knowledge of Intune and Entra administration</p></li><li><p>Experience with PowerShell scripting</p></li><li><p>Good troubleshooting skills for Level 1.5 incidents</p></li><li><p>Experience with Windows endpoint and basic network support</p></li><li><p>Ability to work independently and proactively research solutions</p></li></ul>",
